
[1]crazy

   CRAZY, a.

   1. Broken; decrepit; weak; feeble; applied to the body, or
   constitution, or any structure; as a crazy body; a crazy constitution;
   a crazy ship.

   2. Broken, weakened, or disordered in intellect; deranged, weakened, or
   shattered in mind. We say, the man is crazy.
